---
description: UI/UX development standards
alwaysApply: false
globs: ui_app.py, ui_static/**/*
---

# Cursor Rules: UI/UX Development Standards

rules:
  - id: ui.structure.organization
    description: |
      UI code must be organized consistently.
      - Separate frontend (static files) from backend (Flask app)
      - Place static files in `ui_static/` directory
      - Organize static files by type (CSS, JS, images)
      - Use consistent file naming conventions
      - Document UI component structure
    severity: error

  - id: ui.structure.components
    description: |
      UI components must follow consistent patterns.
      - Use modular component structure
      - Separate concerns (presentation, logic, data)
      - Reuse components when possible
      - Document component APIs and usage
      - Keep components focused and single-purpose
    severity: warning

  - id: ui.communication.api
    description: |
      Frontend-backend communication must follow standards.
      - Use RESTful API endpoints for data operations
      - Use consistent request/response formats
      - Handle API errors gracefully
      - Implement proper error handling and user feedback
      - Use appropriate HTTP methods and status codes
      - Document API endpoints used by UI
    severity: error

  - id: ui.communication.streaming
    description: |
      Streaming responses must be handled properly.
      - Support Server-Sent Events (SSE) for streaming
      - Handle connection errors and reconnection
      - Provide user feedback during streaming
      - Handle partial responses gracefully
      - Document streaming behavior
    severity: warning

  - id: ui.error_handling.user_feedback
    description: |
      Error handling must provide clear user feedback.
      - Display user-friendly error messages
      - Provide actionable error guidance
      - Handle network errors gracefully
      - Show loading states during operations
      - Provide retry mechanisms when appropriate
    severity: error

  - id: ui.error_handling.validation
    description: |
      Input validation must be implemented in UI.
      - Validate user inputs before submission
      - Provide immediate feedback on validation errors
      - Match backend validation rules
      - Display clear validation error messages
      - Prevent invalid form submissions
    severity: error

  - id: ui.testing.requirements
    description: |
      UI components should be tested.
      - Test UI functionality with integration tests
      - Test error handling and edge cases
      - Test responsive design on different screen sizes
      - Test accessibility features
      - Document testing procedures
    severity: warning

  - id: ui.accessibility.standards
    description: |
      UI must be accessible.
      - Use semantic HTML elements
      - Provide alt text for images
      - Ensure keyboard navigation works
      - Maintain sufficient color contrast
      - Support screen readers
      - Test with accessibility tools
    severity: warning

  - id: ui.performance.loading
    description: |
      UI performance must be optimized.
      - Minimize initial page load time
      - Lazy load resources when appropriate
      - Optimize images and assets
      - Use efficient rendering techniques
      - Monitor and optimize performance
    severity: warning

  - id: ui.quality.consistency
    description: |
      UI must be consistent.
      - Use consistent styling and design patterns
      - Maintain consistent user experience
      - Follow established design system
      - Use consistent terminology
      - Document UI patterns and conventions
    severity: warning

  - id: ui.documentation.requirements
    description: |
      UI code must be documented.
      - Document component purpose and usage
      - Document API endpoints used
      - Document user interactions and flows
      - Include inline comments for complex logic
      - Keep documentation up-to-date
    severity: warning

examples:
  - description: "UI error handling pattern"
    language: javascript
    code: |
      /**
       * Handle API errors with user-friendly feedback
       * @param {Error} error - Error object from API call
       * @param {HTMLElement} errorContainer - Container for error message
       */
      function handleApiError(error, errorContainer) {
          let message = "An error occurred. Please try again.";
          let actionable = false;
          
          if (error.status === 401) {
              message = "Authentication required. Please check your API key.";
              actionable = true;
          } else if (error.status === 403) {
              message = "You don't have permission to perform this action.";
          } else if (error.status === 404) {
              message = "The requested resource was not found.";
          } else if (error.status >= 500) {
              message = "Server error. Please try again later.";
          } else if (error.message) {
              message = error.message;
          }
          
          errorContainer.textContent = message;
          errorContainer.style.display = "block";
          
          if (actionable) {
              // Add action button or link
              const actionButton = document.createElement("button");
              actionButton.textContent = "Update API Key";
              actionButton.onclick = () => showApiKeyDialog();
              errorContainer.appendChild(actionButton);
          }
      }

  - description: "Input validation pattern"
    language: javascript
    code: |
      /**
       * Validate form input before submission
       * @param {HTMLFormElement} form - Form element to validate
       * @returns {boolean} True if valid, false otherwise
       */
      function validateForm(form) {
          const errors = [];
          
          // Validate required fields
          const requiredFields = form.querySelectorAll("[required]");
          requiredFields.forEach(field => {
              if (!field.value.trim()) {
                  errors.push({
                      field: field.name,
                      message: `${field.label || field.name} is required`
                  });
                  field.classList.add("error");
              } else {
                  field.classList.remove("error");
              }
          });
          
          // Validate email format
          const emailFields = form.querySelectorAll('input[type="email"]');
          emailFields.forEach(field => {
              if (field.value && !isValidEmail(field.value)) {
                  errors.push({
                      field: field.name,
                      message: "Invalid email format"
                  });
                  field.classList.add("error");
              }
          });
          
          // Display errors
          if (errors.length > 0) {
              displayValidationErrors(errors);
              return false;
          }
          
          return true;
      }

  - description: "Streaming response handling"
    language: javascript
    code: |
      /**
       * Handle streaming API response
       * @param {string} url - API endpoint URL
       * @param {Object} options - Request options
       * @param {Function} onChunk - Callback for each chunk
       * @param {Function} onComplete - Callback on completion
       * @param {Function} onError - Callback on error
       */
      async function streamResponse(url, options, onChunk, onComplete, onError) {
          try {
              const response = await fetch(url, {
                  ...options,
                  headers: {
                      ...options.headers,
                      "Accept": "text/event-stream"
                  }
              });
              
              if (!response.ok) {
                  throw new Error(`HTTP ${response.status}: ${response.statusText}`);
              }
              
              const reader = response.body.getReader();
              const decoder = new TextDecoder();
              
              while (true) {
                  const { done, value } = await reader.read();
                  
                  if (done) {
                      onComplete();
                      break;
                  }
                  
                  const chunk = decoder.decode(value, { stream: true });
                  onChunk(chunk);
              }
          } catch (error) {
              onError(error);
          }
      }

